  ${
    $d f k m n x A $.  $d f m n x B $.  $d f m n x C $.
    $( Equality theorem for sum, when the class expressions ` B ` and ` C ` are
       equal everywhere.  Proved using only Extensionality. $)
    sumeq2w $p |- ( A. k B = C -> sum_ k e. A B = sum_ k e. A C ) $=
