  ${
    $d f j k m n x $.  $d f m n x A $.  $d f m n x B $.  $d f m n x C $.
    cbvsum.1 $e |- ( j = k -> B = C ) $.
    ${
      cbvsum.2 $e |- ( x e. A -> A. k x e. A ) $.
      cbvsum.3 $e |- ( x e. A -> A. j x e. A ) $.
      cbvsum.4 $e |- ( x e. B -> A. k x e. B ) $.
      cbvsum.5 $e |- ( x e. C -> A. j x e. C ) $.
      $( Change bound variable in a sum.  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro,
         13-Jul-2013.) $)
      cbvsum $p |- sum_ j e. A B = sum_ k e. A C $=
        ( vm vf vn cv caddc wcel cc0 wceq wtru cuz cfv wss cz cif cmpt cseq cli
