  ${
    $d k F $.  $d k G $.  $d k M $.  $d k ph $.  $d k Z $.
    abscvgcvg.1 $e |- Z = ( ZZ>= ` M ) $.
    abscvgcvg.2 $e |- ( ph -> M e. ZZ ) $.
    abscvgcvg.3 $e |- ( ( ph /\ k e. Z ) -> ( F ` k ) = ( abs ` ( G ` k ) ) )
        $.
    abscvgcvg.4 $e |- ( ( ph /\ k e. Z ) -> ( G ` k ) e. CC ) $.
    abscvgcvg.5 $e |- ( ph -> seq M ( + , F ) e. dom ~~> ) $.
    $( An absolutely convergent series is convergent.  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 28-Apr-2014.) $)
    abscvgcvg $p |- ( ph -> seq M ( + , G ) e. dom ~~> ) $=
      ( c1 cfv wcel syl cr cc cle wbr wceq cz uzid syl6eleqr cv wa cabs eqeltrd
      cuz abscl 1re a1i cmul eleq2i eqcomd eqle syl2anc recnd breqtrrd sylan2br
      co mulid2 cvgcmpce ) ALBCDEEFGAEEUHMZFAEUANEVCNHEUBOGUCABUDZFNZUEZVDCMZVD
