  ${
    $d k m n x y z A $.  $d n H $.  $d k m n x y z ph $.  $d j k m n x y z Z $.
    $d m n x y z B $.  $d j m n x y z F $.  $d n M $.
    climfsum.1 $e |- Z = ( ZZ>= ` M ) $.
    climfsum.2 $e |- ( ph -> M e. ZZ ) $.
    climfsum.3 $e |- ( ph -> A e. Fin ) $.
    climfsum.4 $e |- ( ( ph /\ k e. A ) -> B e. V ) $.
    climfsum.5 $e |- ( ( ph /\ k e. A ) -> F ~~> B ) $.
    climfsum.6 $e |- ( ph -> H e. W ) $.
    climfsum.7 $e |- ( ( ph /\ ( k e. A /\ n e. Z ) ) -> ( F ` n ) e. CC ) $.
    climfsum.8 $e |- ( ( ph /\ n e. Z ) ->
                      ( H ` n ) = sum_ k e. A ( F ` n ) ) $.
    $( Limit of a finite sum of converging sequences.  Note that ` F ( k ) ` is
       a collection of functions with implicit parameter ` k ` , each of which
       converges to ` B ( k ) ` as ` n ~~> +oo ` .  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 22-Jul-2014.) $)
    climfsum $p |- ( ph -> H ~~> sum_ k e. A B ) $=
      ( wcel vx vy vz vj vm csu cli wbr cv cfv cmpt mpteq2dva wss cfn wi c0 csn
      ssid cun wceq sseq1 sumeq1 mpteq2dv breq12d imbi12d imbi2d cc0 cxp cc 0cn
      cz cuz eqimss2i cvv fvex eqeltri climconst2 sylancr sum0 fconstmpt eqtr4i
      mpteq2i 3brtr4g a1d wn wa ssun1 sstr mpan imim1i sumeq2sdv cbvmptv breq1i
      fveq2 anbi2i csb caddc co simpll syl sumex a1i simprr vex csbeq1a cbvsumi
      ax-17 hbcsb1 syl6breq wral ssun2 simprl syl5ss snss sylibr climcl syl2anc
      ralrimiva ad2antrr hbel eleq1d rcla4 sylc mptex eqid fveq1d syl6eq adantl
      fvmpt hbfv ssfi adantr sselda eqidd fsumsplit csbeq1 sumsn oveq2d eqtrd
      a2d hbbr anassrs an32s sylan fsumcl eqeltrd simplr disjsn adantlr 3eqtr4d
      cin oveq1d climadd ad3antrrr breqtrrd sylan2b exp32 syl5 findcard2s mpcom
